<div class="question-card"><div class="question-header"><span class="q-number">Q 1(1)</span></div><div class="question-body"><div class="question-text"><p>Find the radian measure to the degree measure: 25°</p></div></div><div class="answer-section"><div class="solution-block"><div class="label">Solution</div><div><p>To convert degree measures into radians, we multiply by <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mn>180</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br/><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>∴</mo><msup><mn>25</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mn>25</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mn>180</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>C</mi></msup></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mfrac><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mn>5</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mn>36</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>C</mi></msup></mrow></math></p></div></div></div><div class="question-actions"></div></div>
